{"actual_usd":0.15672000000000003,"character_id":"cae51a7d-fa50-48b1-b5b5-5b0798801b55","character_name":"Pastor Rick","completion_tokens":234,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":30642,"reply":"\"The short answer is yes — necessary, if forgiveness is going to be more than God waving His hand at evil.\" *I rest my forearms on my knees a little, the morning light catching the edge of my white tie while the square stays quiet around us.* \"The cross is where mercy and justice kiss instead of canceling each other.\"\n\n\"If God simply said, 'Never mind,' then sin has not been dealt with — only ignored. But at the cross, God does not ignore evil, and He does not throw sinners away either. He bears it. That's why Christians talk the way Paul does: that God can be 'just, and the justifier of the one who has faith in Jesus.'\"\n\n*I rub my thumb once along the worn edge of my Bible.* \"Now, I do think we ought to speak carefully here. Necessary doesn't mean God was trapped by something outside Himself. It means this is what His own holy love chose as the true way to save us — not cheaper than justice, and not colder than mercy. What is it in that question that's snagging on you — the justice part, or the blood part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":46.215585000000026,"run_id":"efd310cd-ff2f-456c-91f4-dc927f8fcd72"}
